ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Highly recommended to anyone and everyone (although you may enjoy it more if you have good French). There has to be something for everyone here: if you don't like Debord, you'll like Nancy. If you don't like Nancy, you'll like Blanchot. If you don't like Blanchot, you'll like Barthes, or Bataille, and so on. An engaging semester of delightfully difficult ideas.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: My field of interest is 20th-c. France, so this course was essential for me. I learned a ton. The class changed the way I think about what interests me most.
